5: The hour has certainly grown late.
8:
Yet... the moon shines as beautifully
as ever.
11:
You, in the shadows. Do you not also
think so?
14: I finally found you... Katana wielder!
16:
Today, I'll take revenge... for my
father!
19:
Excellent form. However, this is not
enough to take my head.
22:
Apologies, young lady. I cannot be
the target of your revenge, for I am
not a person, nor am I from this
world.
25:
I am Murakumo—blade and spirit.
Nothing more, nothing less.
31: Revenge... You as well, I see...
38:
Awake, are we? Let us have a look at
you, then.
41:
I did not pierce your flesh, but... there
is a great wound in your heart.
Regardless, I am glad you are sound
in body.
44:
You must be hungry. Wait here, and I
shall cook some of my partner's
famous rice porridge for you.
50:
If I had let you die there, still
believing I was a criminal, you would
have returned as a spirit to haunt
me.
53: ...By the way, what is your name?
58:
Well met, Yufir. Focus your energy on
eating and resting for now.
65:
So you're gonna help her search for
her father's actual killer?
68:
At first, she begged me to train her.
One thing led to another, and here
we are.
76:
If matters grow out of hand, then I
would appreciate you giving her a
place to stay. But for now, I do not
wish to distract her with the offer.
79:
More importantly, I need to track
down the killer. The man apparently
uses a katana—a rarity in that town
that should make him stand out.
83:
That's true... Not many people carry
katanas around. Oh, but—
89:
Me? You really suspect me? You're
breaking my poor heart, Alk.
93:
Come on, Zekhel, you know I don't. I
just figured as a katana wielder
yourself, you'd have an idea who
we're looking for.
97:
Hmm, well, you were on the mark
there. I have a feeling you're asking
about Akks, a mercenary from the
Farlands.
100: The thing is... He's already dead.
109:
Oh, I definitely am. I'll never forget
the wild goose chase he led us on.
Plus, it was my own two hands that
cut him down.
113:
I'm curious though. Murakumo, what
would you have done if Akks was still
alive?
116:
Surely you weren't about to have Alk
help you with nasty business like
that.
124:
...This is his wanted poster from back
then.
127: Ah... No... Father! What do I do...
130:
Go home, Yufir. Return to those who
are waiting for you—
135:
That man... He took them all from
me... and I was powerless to stop
him!
136:
So I spent these last ten years
fighting and fighting... I don't even
remember what my father's face
looks like anymore...
144:
I'll bet he does. They'll pay the price
instead of him—
147: Is that what you truly desire?
151:
Very well... Then I shall become a
blade of carnage, absorbing flesh
and blood and reveling in the terror
of your foes.
154:
All manner of shameless fool that
stands before you will fall to me.
158:
Do you have the resolve to wield
such a blade, Yufir?
166:
Do you see now? That is not what
you truly desire.
168:
You should not bind yourself to
oaths that will swallow you whole,
Yufir.
171:
Even you are capable of seeking out
a newer, better path...
174:
You're assuming a lot... I'm not like
you...
176:
I have nothing... I AM nothing... I
should just—
179:
Do not be ridiculous. You have me,
remember?
182:
Your swordsmanship is impressive. If
you combine what you learned from
your father and what you will learn
from me...
184:
You will reach new heights that only
you are capable of reaching. Am I
wrong?
187:
Besides, I am rather fond of the way
you stuff your cheeks with food
while you eat. I would be most
disappointed if I was deprived of the
sight.
196:
Hahahaha, there, there. You have
done well to make it this far.
205:
Wow... I'm amazed at what you
pulled off here, Murakumo.
209:
Hahahaha. Compared to what you
have accomplished, this was
nothing.
212:
Though even I have to admit, I did
not expect to adopt a daughter
devoted to the katana.
221:
That is not to say I am
inexperienced. I have trained many
a wielder. You need not worry.
226:
Hold on, you view her as a
daughter?! But she... No matter how
you flip it, she totally—
230:
What can I say? I cannot help but
wish to be more like you, my partner.
Hahahaha!
236:
Hold on, you don't mean that the
way I think you do... right? Is this
seriously okay?!
